'''JkDefrag''' is a free [[open source]] [[Defragmentation|disk defragmenting utility]] for [[Microsoft Windows|Windows]]. It is the first [[free software]] defragmenting project of its kind. This [[computer program]] was developed by Jeroen Kessels beginning in 2004<ref>Information obtained from product release notes: history.txt file</ref> and is released under the [[GNU]] [[GPL|General Public License]]. In 2008, JkDefrag was re-branded to [[MyDefrag]] by its developer and JkDefrag is no longer supported. Unlike JkDefrag, MyDefrag is closed-source, but still remains free.

'''JkDefrag''' is a free [[open source]] [[Defragmentation|disk defragmenting utility]] for [[Microsoft Windows|Windows]]. It is the first [[free software]] defragmenting project of its kind. This [[computer program]] was developed by Jeroen Kessels beginning in 2004<ref>Information obtained from product release notes: history.txt file</ref> and is released under the [[GNU]] [[GPL|General Public License]].
